German Chemical Workers’ Pay Talks End Without Deal, Union Says

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-03-15T17:05:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/german-chemical-workers-pay-talks-end-without-deal-union-says.html
Discussions between the IG BCE
labor union that represents about 550,000 workers in  Germany ’s
chemical industry and the BAVC chemical-manufacturing employers
association ended today without any agreement on pay.  Talks will resume on March 30 and 31, Hanover, Germany-
based IG BCE said in an e-mailed  statement  today. The union is
demanding a 7 percent wage increase for members, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  